ces/77482/answer",,,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-11","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many contracts (a) his Department and (b) its agencies and non-departmental public bodies (i) have let and (ii) plan to let that are worth (A) between £1 million and £3 million and (B) over £3 million since 2010; how much his Department has spent on monitoring each such contract; and how many officials in his Department monitor each contract.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","205375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77483","Wales Office","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>The Wales Office held one offsite event for staff in 2014 where the Business Plan and the key priorities for the year ahead were reviewed. This had a cost of £319. The Department held no offsite events in 2013.</p><p> </p>","Preseli Pembrokeshire","Stephen Crabb",,"2014-07-17T13:50:30.1841672Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77483/answer","Biography information for Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77483/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77483/answer",,,,,,,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2014-07-11","Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many awaydays his Department has held for officials in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014 to date; and what the cost was of each such event.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Mr Andy Slaughter","205301"
