"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77079","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-21","<p>The Air intelligence, surveillance, target acquisition, and <br>reconnaissance (ISTAR) Optimisation Study (AIOS) is designed to inform decisions on how future Air ISTAR capability, including Maritime Patrol Aircraft, could be delivered. The study is ongoing and activity in the coming months will consider capability requirements and priorities against a range of policy driven scenarios. The AIOS is one of a number of ongoing strands on analysis that will contribute to the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","205174","2014-07-21T15:48:32.841452Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77079/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77079/answer",,,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-10","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what different roles a multi-function maritime patrol aircraft will be required to perform.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","205175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77080","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-21","<p>No decision has been taken to acquire a Maritime Patrol Aircraft. The period from any decision to acquire to entry into service would depend on the platform selected, affordability in the Defence programme and commercial arrangements.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-07-21T15:49:23.2336181Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77080/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77080/answer",,,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-10","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether a maritime patrol aircraft capability will be available for carrier taskforce protection duties by the time that HMS Queen Elizabeth joins the Fleet; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","205176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77081","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-21","<p>Defence Equipment &amp; Support currently offers Mechanical Engineering Craft Apprenticeships at Defence Munitions (DM) Gosport and Technician Apprenticeships at its Headquarters at MOD Abbey Wood, Bristol and at HM Naval Base (HMNB) Devonport. It is planned to recruit for a further Mechanical Engineering Craft Apprenticeship scheme at Defence Munitions Beith from August this year.</p><p> </p><p>The number of Mechanical Engineering Craft Apprenticeships awarded at DM Gosport since 2010 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Male Applicants</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Female Applicants</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Successful Male Applicants</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Successful Female Applicants</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>200</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>204</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>149</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>258</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>138</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The hon. Member may be interested to note over the last three years (2011-2013) 5 of the 10 Apprentice of the Year award winners have been female<br></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of Technician Apprenticeships awarded at MOD Abbey Wood since 2010 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Male Applicants</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Female Applicants</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Successful Male Applicants</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Successful Female Applicants</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>Not available</p></td><td><p>Not available</p></td><td><p>37</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>370</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>36</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>245</p></td><td><p>15</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>260</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>47</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>355</p></td><td><p>29</p></td><td><p>Not yet available</p></td><td><p>Not yet available</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The number of Technician Apprenticeships awarded at HMNB Devonport since 2010 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Male Applicants</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Female Applicants</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Successful Male Applicants</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Number of Successful Female Applicants</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>Not available</p></td><td><p>Not available</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>201</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>115</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>14</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>Not yet available</p></td><td><p>Not yet available</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-07-21T17:00:15.7851499Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77081/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77081/answer","Ludlow","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77081/answer/previousversion/11708","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77081/answer/previousversion/11708","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77081/answer/previousversion/11708","11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-10","Defence Equipment and Support","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) males and (b) females have applied for the DE&S apprenticeship in each year since 2010; and what proportion of such applications have been successful.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","205045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77082","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>All official Ministerial portrait photographs taken since 2010 have been captured by Ministry of Defence civilian and military photographers as part of their normal duties, which have incurred no additional costs. <br><br>Official ministerial portraits, printed when a Secretary of State leaves office, are produced as part of the normal reprographic activity of the Department, incurring estimated costs of less than £10 since 2010.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-07-21T14:03:51.1328589Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77082/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77082/answer",,,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-10","Photographs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent on ministerial portrait photographs in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","205054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77083","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-22","<p>The UK’s military presence east of the Suez Canal is routinely reviewed to ensure that we have the right capabilities to support and achieve our military tasks, such as Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance (ISR) platforms. UK forces contribute to a variety of counter-terrorism, counter-narcotic and security operations. Redeployment from Afghanistan will allow the reallocation of some of these assets to other priority tasks, which includes ISR support.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-07-22T14:00:12.120283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77083/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77083/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77083/answer/previousversion/11729","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77083/answer/previousversion/11729","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77083/answer/previousversion/11729","11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-10","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment his Department has made of the UK's ability to mount persistent and enduring aerial surveillance of strategically important areas east of the Suez Canal after UK withdrawal from Afghanistan; what assets will be required for this purpose after 2015; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","205177"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77084","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-22","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer my predecessor, the right hon. Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Philip Hammond) gave on 23 May 2012 (Official Report, column 722W).</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-07-22T13:57:58.9205455Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77084/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77084/answer","Hansard Extract 23 May 2012 HOC 205160.doc","Hansard Extract 23 May 2012 HOC 205160.doc","Hansard Extract 23 May 2012.","Hansard Extract 23 May 2012.","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77084/answer","Sevenoaks","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77084/answer/previousversion/11727","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77084/answer/previousversion/11727","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77084/answer/previousversion/11727","11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-10","Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answer of 14 November 2011, Official Report, column 526W, on disclosure of information, if he will publish the findings of the inquiry into the unauthorised disclosure of the letter between the former Secretary of State and the Prime Minister which appeared in the Daily Telegraph on 28 September 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","205160"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77085","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-17","<p>Figures on the number of complaints of sexual harassment made by Service personnel since 2010 are published in the Service Complaints Commissioner's (SCC) Annual Reports. The full reports are presented annually to the House and are also located on the SCC website at the following link:<br><br>http://armedforcescomplaints.independent.gov.uk/newsandpublications.htm<br><br>Information on complaints from each service can be found in the relevant pages:<br><br>2013 Annual Report – page 72, appendix 3. <br><br>2012 Annual Report – page 62, appendix 3. <br><br>2011 Annual Report – page 59, appendix 3. <br><br>2010 Annual Report – page 89, appendix 6<br><br>Since 2010, there have been five reported complaints of sexual harassment amongst civilian staff at the Ministry for Defence.<br><br>Due to the small number of cases of sexual harassment reported by Service personnel and civilian staff, providing a breakdown of this information by year might breach Data Protection legislation. The outcome of complaints against sexual harassment is considered sensitive personal data and the disclosure of this information would be unreasonable.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-07-17T16:06:41.6717371Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77085/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77085/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77085/answer","Broxtowe","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77085/answer/previousversion/10493","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77085/answer/previousversion/10493","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77085/answer/previousversion/10493","11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-10","Sexual Harassment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many complaints of sexual harassment have been (a) formally reported and (b) upheld in each service and his Department's Civil Service in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","205161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77086","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-21","<p>Neither the Secretary of State for Defence nor Defence Ministers have met Lord Clanwilliam in the last three years.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-07-21T14:01:15.9190195Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77086/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77086/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77086/answer","Broxtowe","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77086/answer/previousversion/10496","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77086/answer/previousversion/10496","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77086/answer/previousversion/10496","11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-10","Earl Clanwilliam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when (a) he and (b) Ministers in his Department have met Lord Clanwilliam in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","205166"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77087","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-22","<p>67 Army Reservists who returned from operations with injuries have accessed rehabilitation support.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-07-22T16:22:37.7205038Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77087/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77087/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77087/answer","Broxtowe","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77087/answer/previousversion/10495","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77087/answer/previousversion/10495","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77087/answer/previousversion/10495","11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-10","Army Reserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many members of the Army Reserve who returned injured from operations have accessed rehabilitation support.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","205165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77088","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-21","<p>The tri-departmental Conflict Pool in its current form was created in 2010 and is financed from HM Treasury under the Conflict Resources settlement. It is managed tri-departmentally, with resources transferred to the Ministry of Defence (MOD) to fund those projects the MOD will undertake.The Conflict Pool is managed on a regional programme, not country basis.</p><p> </p><p>The MOD has funded projects in all of the Conflict Pool’s five regional programmes: in Afghanistan; in Africa where activity has included work in Nigeria, Somalia and Kenya; in the Middle East and North Africa including projects in Syria, Libya and the Occupied Palestinian Territories; in South Asia where activity has mostly been in Pakistan; and activity through the Wider Europe programme in the Western Balkans, the Caucasus and Central Asia. Activity in all these programmes includes regional, cross-border and multilateral projects therefore data is not held on a purely country basis. The MOD also funds activity through the Strengthening Alliances and Partnerships Programme (SAP).</p><p> </p><p>Regional and thematic figures by programme are below.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2009/10</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Africa</strong></p></td><td><p>£21,955,253</p></td><td><p>£25,155,043</p></td><td><p>£15,349,300</p></td><td><p>£13,969,330</p></td><td><p>£17,451,482</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Afghanistan</strong></p></td><td><p>£1,944,340</p></td><td><p>£3,051,185</p></td><td><p>£515,538</p></td><td><p>£1,296,540</p></td><td><p>£1,022,957</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>MENA</strong></p></td><td><p>£2,896,937</p></td><td><p>£2,675,774</p></td><td><p>£3,371,921</p></td><td><p>£3,804,968</p></td><td><p>£10,945,265</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>South Asia</strong></p></td><td><p>£7,124,261</p></td><td><p>£8,661,400</p></td><td><p>£1,305,900</p></td><td><p>£305,364</p></td><td><p>£494,011</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>SAP*</strong></p></td><td><p>£3,516,826</p></td><td><p>£2,124,898</p></td><td><p>£2,074,708</p></td><td><p>£3,123,000</p></td><td><p>£3,790,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Wider Europe </strong></p></td><td><p>£22,606,731</p></td><td><p>£20,576,782</p></td><td><p>£19,722,746</p></td><td><p>£19,777,805</p></td><td><p>£19,693,366</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong>*Strengthening Alliances and Partnerships Programme; previously Strategic Support to International Organisations Programme </strong></p><p> </p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-07-21T17:02:39.2305056Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77088/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77088/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77088/answer",,,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-10","Conflict Pool","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent from the Conflict Pool in each country in each year since its launch.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","205191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77089","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-15","<p>The Department shares facilities with civilians where feasible (with defence needs taking priority) and will continue to do so for the foreseeable future.</p><p> </p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2014-07-15T15:46:39.9653911Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77089/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77089/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77089/answer",,,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-10","Armed Forces Covenant","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Armed Forces Covenant Annual Report 2013, what steps his Department has taken to improve the sharing of service facilities with civilians.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","205164"
